The paper discusses a novel approach to optimizing deep neural networks through regularization of network architecture. This topic falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The examples used in the paper include deep autoencoder and convolutional neural network, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also mentions sparse linear regression, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.CL, in that order.
